what language comes to stand for in people’s lives. In so doing, she unmasks a social discourse rife with questions of authenticity and cultural politics of inclusion and exclusion. English Heart, Hindi Heartland illustrates how the notion of what is considered to be culturally and linguistically authentic not only obscures larger questions relating to caste, religious, and gender identities, but that the authenticity discourse itself is continually in flux. In order to mediate and extract cultural capital from India’s complex linguistic hierarchies, literary practitioners strategically deploy a fluid set of cultural and political distinctions that Sadana calls "literary nationality." Sadana argues that English, and the way it is positioned among the other Indian languages, does not represent a fixed pole, but rather serves to change political and literary alliances among classes and castes, often in surprising ways.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aBook industries and tradezIndiaxHistoryy20th century. 0aIndic literature (English)y20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aPolitics and literaturezIndiaxHistoryy20th century. 0aPostcolonialism in literature. 0aPostcolonialismzIndia. 0aPublishers and publishingzIndiaxHistoryy20th century. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  aamerican culture vs indian culture.  acomparing different cultures.  acultural authenticity.  adelhi culture.  aeasy to read.  aengaging.  aenglish.  aethnographic study.  aglobalization of english.  agreat for reluctant readers.  ahindi.  ahistory of english.  ahistory of indian culture.  ahistory of indian languages.  ahistory.  aindian culture.  aindian linguistic hierarchies.  alearning from experts.  aleisure reads.  aliterary culture.  aliterary nationality.  